<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="201" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,373,649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,373,399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[403,484,374,400]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,426,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-143@4.[171,1416,417,1772]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–22. Ceratostigma macrostigmatum (Li &amp; Yang, 1987), holotype male. 16. Forewing; 17. Hindwing; 18–19. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 20–21. Hypandrium; 22. Phallosome. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) basal one-fifth with a slightly curved greyish white stripe; radial fork with branches diverging at an angle of about 60°. Epiproct (
<figureCitation box="[654,781,409,435]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,426,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-143@4.[171,1416,417,1772]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–22. Ceratostigma macrostigmatum (Li &amp; Yang, 1987), holotype male. 16. Forewing; 17. Hindwing; 18–19. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 20–21. Hypandrium; 22. Phallosome. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 18–19</figureCitation>
) nearly triangular, pointed at apex, with a nearly U-shaped sclerotized area at base; hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[575,703,445,471]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,426,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-143@4.[171,1416,417,1772]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–22. Ceratostigma macrostigmatum (Li &amp; Yang, 1987), holotype male. 16. Forewing; 17. Hindwing; 18–19. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 20–21. Hypandrium; 22. Phallosome. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 21–22</figureCitation>
) narrowed at apex, with a broad ridge in median area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
